<p>U.S. military aircraft struck two vessels in the eastern Pacific off the coast of South America this week, killing five people and marking the first strikes in the Pacific as part of an expanded Trump administration campaign against alleged drug-smuggling boats [ft.com#1][nytimes.com#1][aljazeera.com#3]. Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth said the operations were carried out at President Trump&#x27;s direction and described the targets as linked to narcotics trafficking and designated terrorist organizations, a claim some regional leaders dispute [allsides.com#1][washingtonpost.com#1]. The moves have increased diplomatic friction with Colombia and drawn sharp rhetoric from both President Trump and Colombian President Gustavo Petro [aljazeera.com#2][thehindu.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/ndXhEbUhXCACr7s0dUnEM0QgLzezEhSOk0S94ewejoeSXd_rxHgrrdmXPRvkwVaKQh4EEvszNmm6Zhub2nAtkq4aIjU4lg7NiPYZV3wI32gtkc0aSK67tHYBEKky_dI3G3YUwm0Py1UAeZrpv5ZxKC_Y7naeUPiXp5a-1HM2rdQQEtRMuOLkK0nHwRc' alt='U.S. troops during a recent training exercise in the Caribbean as the military expands operations in the region' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Pentagon rationale: Defense officials said the strikes targeted vessels their intelligence assessed were carrying narcotics and that operations were ordered by the president, framing the crews as linked to designated terrorist networks [allsides.com#1][ft.com#1].</li><li>Campaign scope: Since September the U.S. has carried out multiple strikes previously confined to the Caribbean; those operations have already resulted in dozens of deaths, and the Pacific attacks broaden the geographic reach of the campaign [guardian.com#1][straitstimes.com#1][aljazeera.com#3].</li><li>Colombian reaction: Colombia&#x27;s president has publicly rebuked U.S. actions and warned of legal steps in U.S. courts, signalling a formal diplomatic and judicial escalation between Bogotá and Washington [aljazeera.com#2][thehindu.com#1].</li><li>Regional tensions: Venezuelan leader Nicolás Maduro responded to the military posture by highlighting his country&#x27;s anti-aircraft capabilities and expanding rhetoric about defence, adding to regional unease [elpais.com#2][firstpost.com#2].</li></ul><blockquote>Yesterday, at the direction of President Trump, the Department of War conducted a lethal kinetic strike on a vessel being operated by a Designated Terrorist Organization and conducting narco-trafficking in the Eastern Pacific. - Pete Hegseth</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>U.S. Department of Defense / Secretary Pete Hegseth: Officials described the strikes as directed by the president, aimed at vessels the U.S. intelligence community assessed were conducting illicit narcotics smuggling and linked to designated terrorist groups [allsides.com#1][ft.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.allsides.com/news/2025-10-22-0700/defense-and-security-us-carries-out-8th-strike-alleged-drug-vessel-time-eastern-pacific-hegseth-says'>AllSides</a>)</li><li>President Gustavo Petro (Colombia): Petro has publicly challenged the U.S. account, traded sharp words with President Trump, and said Colombia may pursue legal remedies in U.S. courts over the operations [aljazeera.com#2][thehindu.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/23/us-colombia-tensions-surge-as-presidents-trump-petro-trade-threats'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li><li>Venezuelan government / President Nicolás Maduro: Maduro warned of strengthened air-defence capabilities and framed the U.S. military presence as a potential threat to regional stability, while denying that Venezuela is the direct target of these specific strikes [elpais.com#2][firstpost.com#2]. (<a href='https://english.elpais.com/international/2025-10-23/maduro-warns-that-he-has-5000-anti-aircraft-missiles-to-guarantee-peace.html'>El País</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.ft.com/content/649621f7-e4ec-408a-9c7f-1814928d9c9c'>US widens campaign against alleged drug traffickers to Paci